      "$cos^{2}\\alpha/2.I$"
    ],
    [
      "$sin^{2}\\alpha/2.A$"
    ],
    [
      "$cos^{2}\\alpha/2.A^{T}$"
    ],
    [
      "$cos^{2}\\alpha/2.A$"
    ]
  ],
  "correctAnswer": 1,
  "explanation": [
    "$AB=I \\implies B = A^{-1}$.",
    "$|A| = 1 + \\tan^2(\\alpha/2) = \\sec^2(\\alpha/2)$.",
    "$A^{-1} = \\frac{1}{|A|} \\text{adj}(A) = \\cos^2(\\alpha/2) \\begin{bmatrix}1 & -\\tan(\\alpha/2) \\\\ \\tan(\\alpha/2) & 1\\end{bmatrix}$.",
    "Note that $A^T = \\begin{bmatrix}1 & -\\tan(\\alpha/2) \\\\ \\tan(\\alpha/2) & 1\\end{bmatrix}$.",
    "Thus, $B = \\cos^2(\\alpha/2) A^T$."
